The Golden Ratio is sometimes called the "divine proportion," because of its frequency in the natural world and can be seen in art, photography, human anatomy and design. The Renaissance artists used the Golden Ratio extensively in their paintings and sculptures to achieve balance and beauty. Even when a person doesn't or can't recognize it, he or she is attracted to it. It naturally provides us with aesthetic visuals, by creating proportion which most individuals find attractive and appealing. The golden ratio is everywhere, existing in natural forms such as shells, flowers, galaxies ‚Äî even the human face.
